{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:03:39.047417+00:00", "update": {"tools": {"messages": [{"type": "tool", "data": {"content": [{"type": "text", "text": "successfully downloaded text file (SHA: b31dcaee641dae642e277a9d9dd36222f3ddc362)", "id": "lc_4073b819-5552-4100-ad3d-f3d8f7f1027c"}, {"type": "text", "text": "\"\"\"Thin wrappers around git subprocess calls used by gwc.\"\"\"\nfrom __future__ import annotations\n\nimport subprocess\n\n\ndef _git(*args: str) -> str:\n    return subprocess.check_output([\"git\", *args], text=True).strip()\n\n\ndef status_summary() -> str:\n    branch = _git(\"rev-parse\", \"--abbrev-ref\", \"HEAD\")\n    try:\n        upstream = _git(\"rev-parse\", \"--abbrev-ref\", f\"{branch}@{{upstream}}\")\n        ahead_behind = _git(\"rev-list\", \"--left-right\", \"--count\", f\"{upstream}...{branch}\")\n        behind, ahead = ahead_behind.split()\n        tracking = f\"(ahead {ahead}, behind {behind})\"\n    except subprocess.CalledProcessError:\n        tracking = \"(no upstream)\"\n\n    porcelain = _git(\"status\", \"--porcelain\").splitlines()\n    staged = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line and line[0] != \" \" and line[0] != \"?\")\n    unstaged = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line and line[1] != \" \")\n    untracked = sum(1 for line in porcelain if line.startswith(\"??\"))\n    return f\"{branch}  {tracking}  staged={staged} unstaged={unstaged} untracked={untracked}\"\n\n\ndef list_merged_branches(protected: list[str]) -> list[str]:\n    out = _git(\"branch\", \"--merged\", \"main\")\n    branches = [line.strip().lstrip(\"* \").strip() for line in out.splitlines()]\n    return [b for b in branches if b and b not in protected]\n\n\ndef delete_branch(name: str) -> None:\n    subprocess.check_call([\"git\", \"branch\", \"-d\", name])\n", "id": "lc_4e2228db-f2aa-4ac9-bef0-9a5d3c91a660"}], "additional_kwargs": {}, "response_metadata": {}, "type": "tool", "name": "get_file_contents", "id": "28ab8ec3-be8d-4a36-b48f-047909787d7c", "tool_call_id": "call_2ce6d1e41c9c461c8d8e0cc9", "artifact": null, "status": "success"}}]}}}
{"ts": "2026-06-09T00:03:58.844159+00:00", "update": {"model": {"messages": [{"type": "ai", "data": {"content": "Based on my exploration of the repository, here's what I found:\n\n## Command-Line Tool: `gwc`\n\nThe package installs a command called **`gwc`** (Git Workflow Companion), as specified in `pyproject.toml`:\n\n```toml\n[project.scripts]\ngwc = \"gwc.cli:main\"\n```\n\n## What `gwc` Does\n\nThe `gwc` command provides several subcommands for git workflow assistance:\n\n### 1. `gwc status-summary`\nPrints a one-line summary of the current branch state, showing:\n- Current branch name\n- Upstream tracking status (ahead/behind counts)\n- Counts of staged, unstaged, and untracked files\n\n### 2. `gwc branch-name <issue_number> <slug>`\nGenerates a conventional branch name for an issue. Default format: `issue-{number}-{slug}` (e.g., `issue-123-fix-login-bug`).\n\n### 3. `gwc clean-merged [--apply]`\nLists local branches fully merged into main. By default, it shows what *would* be deleted (dry-run). Use `--apply` to actually delete the branches.\n\n### Additional Features\n- `--version` flag shows `gwc 0.1.0`\n- Configuration can be loaded to customize behavior (e.g., branch name prefix, protected branches list)\n\nThe tool is described as \"small, local-only git helpers\" and is still in early development (version 0.1.0).", "additional_kwargs": {"refusal": null}, "response_metadata": {"token_usage": {"completion_tokens": 542, "prompt_tokens": 5499, "total_tokens": 6041, "completion_tokens_details": {"accepted_prediction_tokens": null, "audio_tokens": 0, "reasoning_tokens": 222, "rejected_prediction_tokens": null, "image_tokens": 0}, "prompt_tokens_details": {"audio_tokens": 0, "cached_tokens": 4992, "cache_write_tokens": 0, "video_tokens": 0}, "cost": 0, "is_byok": true, "cost_details": {"upstream_inference_cost": 0.0007100562, "upstream_inference_prompt_cost": 0.0002385162, "upstream_inference_completions_cost": 0.00047154}}, "model_provider": "openai", "model_n